'''James Bayley''' (15 November 1899 – 1981) was an Australian male [[tennis]] player who represented Australian in the [[Olympic Games]]. He competed in the [[Tennis at the 1924 Summer Olympics – Men's singles|singles event]] at the [[1924 Summer Olympics]], reaching the third round in which he lost to [[Brian Gilbert (tennis)|Brian Gilbert]]. With compatriot [[James Willard]] he competed in the [[Tennis at the 1924 Summer Olympics – Men's doubles|men's doubles event]] and reached the second round.<ref name=sportsreference>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ba/james-bayley-1.html |title=Olympic Sports – Athletes – James Bayley |work=sports-reference.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922114217/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ba/james-bayley-1.html |archivedate=22 September 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=James Bayley – Olympic Results|url=http://corporate.olympics.com.au/B619599C-48E8-411C-A6F6073EA3991FF9|publisher=Australian Olympic Committee}}</ref>
He competed in the [[1924 Wimbledon Championships]] and reached the third round in the singles event and lost in the first round of the doubles and mixed doubles event.<ref>{{cite web|title=Wimbledon players archive – James Bayley|url=http://www.wimbledon.com/en_GB/scores/draws/archive/players/081c2b46-ca4f-48a9-a1ec-cfa1c4ad3307/index.html|publisher=AELTC}}</ref>
